Drain the @Grilling Cheese{200%grams} then cut into slices (3 per person). Place in a
#bowl{} of cold @Water{to taste}.

Cut the @Tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Bash or roughly chop the @Hazelnuts{10%grams}.

Place a pan (preferably non-stick) over medium heat (without oil). Dry-fry the
hazelnuts until toasted, stirring regularly, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the
pan and set aside.

> TIP: Watch them closely—they can burn easily.

Remove the cheese slices from the water and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}. Once hot,
add the cheese and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, make a dressing by mixing the @Cranberry Chutney{1%sachet}
with 1 tbsp oil.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the pit. Cut into chunks (while still in its
skin) then use a #spoon{} to scoop it out into the bowl with the dressing.

Add the tomato and @Salad Leaves{40%grams} to the bowl and toss to coat in the
dressing. Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Divide the salad between bowls.

Top with the pan-fried cheese and toasted hazelnuts.